column1: Dude, check out all the booths!

As one might expect from Sendai's Tanabata
festival. It's quite lively here.

Apparently, the locals call it "Tanabata-san."
And it's said to have originated from back in
Date Masamune's time.
Hey, that's the dude from the statue, huh?

He is not a "dude." He is Lord Date Masamune,
the One-Eyed Dragon of Oshu.
Geez, what are you, his retainer or somethin'?

There're so many booths. It's hard to pick
what to see first. What do you think,
[1B]S1?
I want to check out the masks.

I'm cool with that. I dunno why, but yakisoba
from a food stand always tastes so friggin' good.

Let's hold off on the food for now. I want to
check out all the booths with Lady Ann first.

Oh, wanna make a competition out of it? I'm a
pretty good shot, you know.

You seem more like the brute force type, Ryuji.
I think you should stick to melee weapons.
I don't think we're on the same page here...

Ah, yes. Perhaps it's our experience with them
in the Metaverse, but they always manage to
catch my eye.

Tellin' me. I already bought one. Reminds me of
when I was a kid.
Speakin' of which, ain't those guys here yet?

It takes time for a lady to get ready. They're not
unrefined apes like the rest of you.

Who you callin' an ape? You're the unrefined
one, ya furball!
Well, this furball's got claws, ya bonehead!
Oh, Lady Ann! You look absolutely gorgeous!
Sorry. Tying the obi took quite some time.
Can I get a closer look?

Right, this outfit was made to be worn during
the summer, and it matches the festival
atmosphere perfectly.
Thanks. It means a lot, hearing that from you.
S-Stop staring so much. It's embarrassing!

Absolutely picturesque. You've brought us a
much needed air of refinement.

Yeah, according to someone, we're about as
unrefined as it gets...

Wow, Ryuji, that looks really good on you. Even
better than your school uniform!
You don't gotta try'n make me feel better!

You made a good choice with that mask, though.
Yellow's a good match for this season.

I bought a water balloon, myself! You gotta get
one when you go to a festival.
Water balloon? Oh, you mean a "yo-yo."
No, isn't that called a "water yo-yo"?
Wait a sec, I thought it was "yo-yo balloon."

Yeah! I knew it! I mean, it's only a little bit,
but there's still SOME water inside!

See, told you! Water balloons and yo-yo's are
two totally different things. So it's gotta be a
yo-yo balloon!

*chuckle* It looks like everyone's having a
good time.

We should have a little fun ourselves. Why don't
we check out the food stands and get something
to eat?

Sure. I was starting to get hungry since
everything smells so good.

Look! They've got all the staples! Yakisoba,
yakitori, shaved ice... They've even got konjac
skewers! Those are huge in Tohoku!
What are we waiting for!? Chaaarge!
Come on, we should get going too. I'm starving.

Hell yeah! Let's start from one end and get one
of everything!

It feels as if we're forgetting the spirit of
Tanabata... though I have no objections.

I want to see more of the festival too. Show me
how to catch goldfish, [1B]S1.
I had fun with everyone at the festival...
